  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-surrogate hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether a neural-network surrogate trained on CFD-derived hemolysis data can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results are reported from two training runs whose point-estimate metrics are declared in agreement; no seed-to-seed variance characterisation, ensemble statistics, or model-variance UQ is provided.",
