    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-ml-hemolysis-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The ML surrogate demonstrates point-estimate agreement with experimental hemolysis measurements within the 10 % acceptance criterion at all five COU operating points. Two independent training runs (seeds 42 and 117) produced R² values of 0.961 and 0.958 respectively, which the assessment team characterises as confirming model stability. The surrogate is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device and supporting the RH < 1 regulatory comparison.",
